Diagnosis.
Body length 
5.6–8.3 mm
(
Figs 7–8
). Pronotum with distinct tufts of black scales on either side of middle on anterior margin, laterally and on midline just anterior to midlength. Femora each with 2 distinctly separated teeth. Elytra with strial punctures large and deep, at least some wider than width of adjacent elytral intervals; with concentrations of black erect scales on intervals 3 and 5 throughout basal 2/3 of length; apical 1/3 of elytra with bright white scales distinctly contrasting with dark scales on rest of elytra. Male ventrite 5 (
Fig. 14
) flat, not modified; ventrite 1 longitudinally impressed medially. Aedeagus (
Fig. 19
).
